title: H.S. football: Coming attractions
text:
October 26, 2015 Last updated: Monday, October 26, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
Coming attractions 
No. 3 Mahwah (7-0) at No. 2 River Dell (7-0), Friday, 6 p.m.: The Mahwah defense, which has posted four straight shutouts, will get tested in a showdown that'll crown the Big North Patriot Division champion. 
No. 4 Ramapo (6-1) at No. 5 Pascack Valley (6-1), Friday, 6 p.m.: The visiting Green Raiders have won five straight. Another win would move them ahead of Pascack Valley in the North 1, Group 3 power-point standings. 
No. 11 (5-2) Ridgewood at No. 6 Passaic Tech (6-1), Friday, 7 p.m.: The winner of this Big North, non-division game will earn the top seed in North 1, Group 5. 
Mountain Lakes (5-2) at No. 15 Pequannock (6-1), Friday, 7 p.m.: Pequannock will look to extend its winning streak to six games against a perennial Morris County power. 
No. 5 DePaul (2-5) at No. 3 Paramus Catholic (3-4), Saturday, 4 p.m.: Paramus Catholic needs to win this Big North United Division encounter to secure its place in the Non-Public, Group 4 playoffs. 
No. 1 Bergen Catholic (5-2) at No. 4 Don Bosco (4-3), Saturday, 7 p.m.: The Crusaders can clinch the Big North United title by winning this road game. The top seed in the Non-Public, Group 4 playoffs also is in play.
